article.headline: Oral Roberts 67, W. Illinois 60
article.story: MACOMB, Ill. (AP) -- Caleb Green scored 19 points and grabbed 10 rebounds Saturday to lead Oral Roberts to a 67-60 win over Western Illinois. The Golden Eagles (16-8, 8-1 Mid-Continent) led 27-21 at halftime and never trailed in the second half, when they led by as many as 14 with 11:33 remaining. Oral Roberts outrebounded the Leathernecks 33-26 and outscored Western Illinois in the paint 32-21. Oral Roberts shot 51.2 percent from the floor, while Western Illinois shot just 30.6 percent, going 5-for-17 from 3-point range. The teams combined to attempt 57 free throws; the Golden Eagles went 22-of-26 from the line, and Western Illinois converted 25-of-31. Ken Tutt added 14 points and five rebounds for the Golden Eagles. Sammy Hunter scored 16 points to lead Western Illinois.
